General Disclosures
The Platform is hosted in the United States. If you are visiting the Platform from outside of the United States, please note that by providing us your information it is being stored or processed in the United States where our data center and servers are located and operated. This section sets forth the general Privacy Policy for the United States and other jurisdictions not otherwise specifically covered by the other jurisdiction-specific policies.
Depending on your state or country of residence, applicable privacy laws may provide you with a right to additional disclosures as well as special consumer rights. If you are outside of the United States, please also see the provisions in our International Privacy Policy. If you are outside the United States and do not wish to allow the transfer of your personal information to the United States, you should not use this Platform and you should opt-out of the collection of cookies by following the guidelines in our section titled How To Restrict Cookies. For more information about how we utilize cookies, view our Cookie Policy.
What Information We Collect And For What Purpose
Category of Information
Examples
Purpose of Collection
Online Identifier
the information we may collect includes your IP address (a number that is automatically assigned to your computer whenever you connect to the Internet)
we may collect this information to maintain the security of the Platform by stopping “denial of service” attacks as well as preventing bot activity
Platform
Cookies
the information we may collect includes:
your language preference for the Platform
whether or not you have accepted the Platform’s terms of use
other cookies, as shown in the cookie table of Cookie Policy at the end of this Policy
we may collect this information in order to:
