the date and time of access to the Platform
the sub-pages within the Platform visited
referral website information
we may collect this information in order to:
measure, track and analyze trends and usage in connection with the use of our Platform
see how we can better optimize our Platform
maintain and improve our Platform
We also may collect and retain search parameter data, such as the sport nationality, role, sport, country of purchase, or other search terms. We also may collect and retain the results of the searches as well as metrics relating to these searches, such as the date and time of the search. However, this search data is not associated with your personal information.
Within the past twelve months, we may have collected your e-mail address for the purpose of responding to your questions or concerns. However, as of the effective date of this Privacy Policy, Global DRO no longer collects e-mail address.
To Whom Do We Disclose Your Information And Why
The personal information that we collect from you through this Platform is only used for our own internal purposes as described in this Privacy Policy and will not be publicly disclosed. We do not sell your personal information. However, we utilize a number of service providers to help maintain the Platform and provide the associated search functionality. Below is a list of those entities to whom we may disclose your personal information.
Database Hosting Vendor.  Like many organizations, we utilize cloud databases to host our data, including your personal information, so that we can effectively and safely operate the Platform.
Auditors.  We may be subject to audits from a number of entities, such as our regulators or service providers, as well as due to our own internal auditing policies. In order to accomplish an effective audit, we must provide information, which may include your personal information, to external auditors. We always ensure that your information is safely disclosed and stored and that auditors can only use your information for the purposes of completing an audit.
Analytics Providers.  We may utilize analytics service providers to measure the performance of the Platform and to help us optimize the Platform’s functionality.
Corporate Transactions.  We may share all or part of your personal information with other entities in connection with the sale, assignment, merger or other transfer of all or a portion of our organization or assets to such entities (including due to a sale in connection with a bankruptcy). We will require any such purchaser, assignee or other successor organization to honor the terms of this Privacy Policy.
Legal Purposes.  We may disclose all or part of your personal information when we have reason to believe that disclosing this information is necessary to identify, contact or bring legal action against someone who may be violating any agreement with us, or may be causing injury to or interference with (either intentionally or unintentionally) our rights or property, other users of the Platform, or anyone else that could be harmed by such activities. We may disclose information in response to a subpoena, search warrant, in connection with judicial proceedings, or pursuant to court orders, (disciplinary) legal process or other law enforcement measures. We may disclose or access personal information when we believe in good faith that the law requires it, to establish our legal rights or to defend against legal claims, and for administrative and other purposes that we deem necessary to maintain, service and improve our Platform.
Global DRO Member Organizations. We may disclose information that we collect through this Platform to the other Global DRO member organizations and licensees.
If you choose to provide one of the Global DRO member organizations with personal information by connecting with the organization directly via email, that personal information will be handled in accordance with each national anti-doping agency’s respective data privacy practices, not Global DRO’s data privacy practices. We encourage you to carefully review the privacy policy of each entity to which you provide information.
Links To Other Sites
This Platform has links to other websites. Once you link to another site, you are subject to the privacy policy of the new site and its operator. We encourage you to carefully review the privacy policy of each entity to which you provide information.
How Long We Retain Your Information
We may retain your personal information for as long as is necessary to achieve the purposes as stated in the section of this Policy titled
What Information We Collect And For What Purpose
, but in all cases, for a period of time that is consistent with applicable law, applicable statute of limitations and our data retention practices. You can find how long cookies are retained in the cookie table at the end of this Privacy Policy.
Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA)
The Children’s Online Privacy and Protection Act (COPPA) regulates online collection of information from persons under the age of 13. It is our policy to refrain from knowingly collecting or maintaining personal information relating to any person under the age of 13. If you are under the age of 13, please do not supply any personal information through the Platform. If you are under the age of 13 and have already provided personal information through the Platform, please have your parent or guardian contact us immediately using the information provided under Contact Us so that we can remove such information from our files.
Your Rights With Respect To Personal Information
With regards to the personal information that is collected through the Platform, you have the right to be informed about the who, what, why and how relating to the processing of your personal information. Please refer to the table of contents at the beginning of this Privacy Policy to quickly find the specific disclosures relating to your right to be informed. Further, you may have the ability to request: (i) confirmation regarding whether or not Global DRO currently has or processes personal information about you; (ii) a copy of the personal information that Global DRO has or processes about you in a readily intelligible format; and (iii) to have your personal information rectified, amended, blocked or deleted if our processing of your personal information is inaccurate, incomplete, or excessive. You can request to exercise these rights by following the instructions provided under Contact Us. Please be as specific as possible in your request.
However, we may not be able to comply with your request for a number of reasons:
the information that you request is not subject to the Global DRO obligation that grants you the right to make a request in relation to your personal information;
we are not able to comply with your request without incurring disproportionate burden or expense; or
if complying with your request conflicts with the integrity of the anti-doping system or an Anti-Doping Organization's ability to plan or conduct No Advance Notice Testing or to investigate and establish anti-doping rule violations or other legal claims.
If any of the above reasons apply, we will let you know in our response to your request. You have the right to initiate a complaint with your country’s national anti-doping agency as stated in the section titled Contact Us. If your compliant is not resolved, you may notify the World Anti-Doping Agency of your complaint through .
Note that we may be required to gather additional information from you in order to process your request. We will only use this information in the context of evaluating and responding to your request.
Changes To This Privacy Policy
We may amend this Privacy Policy at any time by posting revisions on our Platform. If we make any material changes in the way we process your information, we will notify you by prominently posting notice of the changes on our Platform.
